       for a rapidly changing America.
     * Is Copper a Cause of Alzheimer’s Disease?
    Is Copper a Cause of Alzheimer’s Disease?
       With $1.9 million from the National Institute of General Medical
       Sciences, a University of Houston chemist is exploring the link
       between copper protein molecules in brain cells and
       neurodegenerative diseases like Alzheimer’s.

